This paper is about optimization algorithms for deep learning models, which is a topic that falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the convergence rate of optimization algorithms for training machine learning models. The second likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper specifically mentions deep learning models and their optimization. The third likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as optimization algorithms are crucial for training computer vision models. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as optimization is a fundamental problem in AI and machine learning. The fifth likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as optimization algorithms are a type of algorithm and this paper proposes a new algorithm for optimization.
